The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a visit to Lordstown, Ohio. The President discusses an innovative electric pickup truck being produced in the area, which features motors in each wheel. He praises the technology and its potential advantages, such as improved traction and increased interior space. Other speakers at the event, including Senator Portman and local representatives, express excitement about the economic growth and job opportunities brought by the production of the electric vehicle and batteries in the area. The President highlights the partnership between the government, General Motors, and the company producing the electric truck. The remarks conclude with the President expressing anticipation for an upcoming debate and briefly addressing a tweet about releasing a financial statement.